main event: A bright bluish-white unidentified flying object was observed in Windsor, Newfoundland on October 19, 1952.
interesting points: The object was stationary for a considerable amount of time before moving rapidly in a straight course to the north-northwest.,The observation lasted between 10 to 15 minutes.,The object was described as flaring and pulsating at irregular intervals.,Initially, it appeared to be a Saturnoid-type object, but could possibly be a meteor or distant flare.,No photographs were included in the report.
